long_description:
The Outside Lands Music and Arts Festival isn’t your typical music fest. The two-day gathering is a celebration of Northern California ingenuity, featuring foodfare from James Beard-award-winning chefs, regional wines, craft brews, and music all set in the lush Golden Gate Park in San Francisco. There’s really no other fest like it. 

At Stanford Court Hotel, we’re excited about the Outside Lands Music & Arts Festival. For one, our friends at Seven Stills Brewery & Distillery will be one of 30 featured breweries pouring in the designated “Beer Lands” tent during the event; we’re also offering guests attending the festival a 20-percent discount upon booking. See details here.

 

Finally, amid all the excitement with headliners like Florence & the Machine and queen of pop Janet Jackson, we suggest you keep an eye out for these up-and-coming artists at Outside Lands this year.

Caleborate

Based out of Berkeley, this Bay Area rapper became a local sensation after the 2016 release of his album, “1993.” Caleborate is an industry outsider who often questions current trends in his songs. Pigeons & Planes writer Jacob Moore describes his work as, “smart, introspective hip-hop that doesn't reveal itself fully upon first listen.” The 25-year old just released his album “Real Person” earlier this year – check out tracks on SoundCloud.

Tash Sultana

The independent Melbourne-born one-woman-band is not something you see everyday. Her vocals are as playful as her noodling guitar riffs and she builds music with the use of a step pedal as she goes. Tash Sultana’s playing passion is infectious and her dynamic range is unforgettable. Check out her Tiny Desk Concert to get an idea of her work. Don’t miss this performance!

[SF Music Venues We Love] 

Illenium

This bass-heavy, SF-raised producer is making waves in the electronic music world. His 2017 sophomore album “Awake” made it onto Billboard's Top 200 and he was named “Electronic Music’s Next Biggest Star” by Forbes magazine earlier this year. Illenium has recently enjoyed sold-out shows and is expected to draw a diverse crowd to the stage during this year’s Outside Lands Festival.

Sabrina Claudio

The young Sabrina Claudio is new on the scene, but her sensual R&B songs quickly caught widespread attention. Her debut mixtape peaked 13 on Billboard’s Top R&B Albums; this year she released singles “All to You” and “Don’t Let Me Down” featuring popular singer Khalid. She received backlash from fans earlier this year for foolish commentary on Twitter, which Claudio is still in the midst of surpassing. Her upcoming studio album is expected to be released later this year. Amid immediate success met with prompt criticism, see what the unique Claudio brings to the stage for Outside Lands this year. 

[Local SF Record Stores and All Things Vinyl]

Cuco

The 19-year-old chicano from south L.A. recently came onto the scene in a similar fashion as Toro y Moi, but Cuco enjoys an Odd Future-like perversion. Ironic lyrics, whacky music videos and a humorous blase/DIY attitude makes the artist just as interesting as his music. Cuco best describes his music as “alternative dream pop.” Earlier this year he released a short EP, “Chiquito” and now occasionally tours with Kali Uchis. There’s no telling where Cuco will go – make sure to check out his set and see what you think.

Attending Outside Lands this year? Check out our Outside Lands booking promotion.

--

Stanford Court is a boutique hotel located in Nob Hill. Close to Chinatown, Union Square, and North Beach, Stanford Court Hotel offers free bike rentals to make every part of San Francisco accessible to our guests.
